Package com.backend.boilerplate.util

Class SynchronizedInMemoryCache<K,​T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.backend.boilerplate.util.SynchronizedInMemoryCache<K,​T>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of keys maintained by this cache
    T - the type of mapped values
    public class SynchronizedInMemoryCache<K,​T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Custom implementation of Apache commons LRUMap LRUMap.

    All operations on this cache object are synchronized over this LRUMap see cacheMap.

    Implemented with optional async process to clear cached objects which are not accessed in last timeToLive milliseconds. Given timerInterval value, every instance will create one Daemon thread Thread which regularly triggers cleanup process after every timerInterval seconds. see SynchronizedInMemoryCache(long, long, int) see cleanup()

    All arguments to all task methods must be non-null.

    Author:
    sarvesh

    • Method Detail

      • put

        public void put​(K key,
                T value)
        Maps the specified key to the specified value in this table. Neither the key nor the value can be null.

        The value can be retrieved by calling the get method with a key that is equal to the original key.

        Parameters:
        key - key with which the specified value is to be associated
        value - value to be associated with the specified key. This is value is wrapped into instance of CacheObject see SynchronizedInMemoryCache.CacheObject
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the specified key or value is null

      • get

        public T get​(K key)
        Returns the value to which the specified key is mapped..

        More formally, if this map contains a mapping from a key k to a value v such that key.equals(k), then this method returns v. (There can be at most one such mapping.)

        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the specified key is null
        See Also:
